				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952#post-4739411</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952/scp-5191#post-4739411</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 05 Aug 2020 17:14:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tao McCawley</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3212944</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>In the last log, the designer child started crying because they weren't happy and realized they weren't loved, just displayed.</p> <p>Instead of comforting the child and asking what was wrong, the &quot;parent&quot; called the factory and asked them to fix it.</p> <p>Those designer kids are still kids, and this parent is touting them like a trophy rather than giving them the love and support they need.</p> <p>This is a good skip for sure, heart-wrenching, but good.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952#post-4731271</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952/scp-5191#post-4731271</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 27 Jul 2020 16:58:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I feel like this has the potential to be pitch-black disturbing but doesn’t take things to their natural conclusions. There’s a great evil oozing out of so much here but we never really get to see it until the end and by that point it’s taken so long that it’s no longer lingering dread but anxious boredom. Cutting down the excess material here would go a long way.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952#post-4730324</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952/scp-5191#post-4730324</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 26 Jul 2020 18:45:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DianaBerry</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3444428</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I agree with the above comments that it would have helped if you had paced the entries a bit better. Maybe starting out with the most normal, and gradually escalating to horribly disturbing. That said, that isn't enough to halt my upvote. This is a very disturbing piece, and I adore horror in weird ways, which this very much is. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
