					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952#post-4729848</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13584952/scp-5191#post-4729848</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 26 Jul 2020 07:49:14 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheMightyMcB</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4483018</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>That last note hedges into discomforting territory, but I don't think it carries the concept far enough to sustain itself on the shock value of purchasing designer babies alone. Additionally, the notes before the last one were uninteresting and didn't really buy you all that much. One or two fairly mundane orders would be fine before moving on to the uncomfortable stuff, but five was far too many entries with little to no escalation.</p> <p>-1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
